== Seasonal Word ==
As a {{ill|kigo|ja|季語|12=draft}}, the term '''Haru Matsuri''' (春祭り) represents a seasonal word for spring (either for {{ill|early spring|ja|初春|12=draft}} or the three months of spring, depending on the {{ill|saijiki|ja|歳時記|12=draft}}).<ref name="Kigosai">{{Cite web|和書|date=2011-02-16 |url=http://kigosai.sub.jp/kigo500e/341.html |title=春祭 |work=Kigosai Saijiki |publisher=Kigosai Saijiki Association |accessdate=2018-02-17}}</ref> It falls under the classification of {{ill|events|ja|行事|12=draft}} or human affairs.<ref>"Events" and "human affairs" refer here to activities performed by humans.</ref> In terms of seasonal words, it encompasses festivals held during the spring season.<ref name="Kigosai" />
{{quotation|
* Example: The '''Haru Matsuri''' begins with the sprouting of old mulberries – {{ill|Shūson Mizuhara|ja|水原秋桜子|12=draft}}<ref name="Daijisen" />
* Example: '''Haru Matsuri''' beneath the mountains, few fresh monpe in sight – {{ill|Hakyō Ishida|ja|石田波郷|12=draft}}
* Example: Valleys open to the sight of Norikura at '''Haru Matsuri''' – {{ill|Fura Maeda|ja|前田普羅|12=draft}} 『Hida Tsumugi』 (published 1947)<ref name="Kigosai" />
