{{afc comment|Wikidata entry (none) Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 05:12, 12 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{afc comment|Wikidata entry (none) Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 06:31, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{afc comment|Wikidata entry (none) Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 03:21, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} [[File:Aoi Matsuri.jpg|thumb|230px|[[:en:Aoi Matsuri|Aoi Matsuri]] (the {{ill|Reisai|ja|例祭|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Reisai|qq=}} of [[:en:Shimogamo Shrine|Kamo Shrine]] and [[:en:Kamigamo Shrine|Kamo-wakeikazuchi Shrine]])]] [[File:神楽台 (岐阜県高山市) - panoramio (2).jpg|thumb|230px|{{ill|Hie Shrine (Takayama)|ja|日枝神社 (高山市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hie Shrine (Takayama)|qq=|1=Hie Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11509534}} Reisai "Haru no Sannō Matsuri" (part of [[:en:Takayama Festival|Takayama Festival]])]] [[File:はやし屋台.JPG|thumb|230px|{{ill|Hitaka Shrine|ja|日高神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hidaka Shrine|qq=}} Reisai (part of {{ill|Hitaka Hibuse Festival|ja|日高火防祭り|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hitaka Hibuse Festival|qq=}})]] [[File:Okunitama-jinja-30.jpg|thumb|230px|[[:en:Ōkunitama Shrine|Okunitama Shrine]] Reisai (part of {{ill|Kurayami Festival|ja|くらやみ祭|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurayami Festival|qq=|1=Kurayami Matsuri|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11265601}})]]
'''Spring Matsuri''' (春祭)<ref name="Daijisen">『[[:en:Daijisen|Daijisen]]』</ref><ref>Heibonsha 『{{ill|MyPedia|ja|マイペディア|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/MyPedia|qq=|1=My Pedia|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11339782}}』</ref><ref>Heibonsha 『[[:en:Heibonsha World Encyclopedia|Sekai Daihyakka Jiten]]』, 2nd Edition</ref><ref>Shogakukan 『[[:en:Encyclopedia Nipponica|Nipponica]]』</ref>, also called '''Spring Festival''' or '''Haru no Matsuri''' (はるまつり), is a general term for [[:en:Festival|festivals]] held in the [[:en:Spring (season)|spring]].
== Seasonal Word == As a [[:en:Kigo|kigo]], the term '''Spring Matsuri''' (春祭り) represents a seasonal word for spring (either for {{ill|early spring|ja|初春|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/early spring|qq=|1=Hatsuharu|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q16870571}} or the three months of spring, depending on the [[:en:Saijiki|saijiki]]).<ref name="Kigosai">{{Cite web|和書|date=2011-02-16 |url=http://kigosai.sub.jp/kigo500e/341.html |title=春祭 |work=Kigosai Saijiki |publisher=Kigosai Saijiki Association |accessdate=2018-02-17}}</ref> It falls under the classification of {{ill|events|ja|行事|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/events|qq=|1=events|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11625998}} or human affairs.<ref>"Events" and "human affairs" refer here to activities performed by humans.</ref> In terms of seasonal words, it encompasses festivals held during the spring season.<ref name="Kigosai" /> {{quotation| * Example: The '''Spring Matsuri''' begins with the sprouting of old mulberries – [[:en:Shūōshi Mizuhara|Shūson Mizuhara]]<ref name="Daijisen" /> * Example: '''Spring Matsuri''' beneath the mountains, few fresh monpe in sight – [[:en:Ishida Hakyō|Hakyō Ishida]] * Example: Valleys open to the sight of Norikura at '''Spring Matsuri''' – {{ill|Fura Maeda|ja|前田普羅|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fura Maeda|qq=|1=Fura Maeda|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11397594}} 『Hida Tsumugi』 (published 1947)<ref name="Kigosai" /> * Example: Shellfish alive in a tank at '''Spring Matsuri''' – Yaehiro Hiroe 『Chikuma Literary Anthology』<ref name="Kigosai" /> }} There are no sub-seasonal words for it. While no directly related seasonal words are listed, many spring festivals, such as the [[:en:Kinen-sai|Kinensai]], are seasonal words, which naturally relate to Spring Matsuri.
